verbose_text: Our finding that treatment of cells with structurally diverse class I selective PI3K inhibitors that do not inhibit Vps34 induce a ~ 40% reduction in SGK3 activity at doses that suppress Akt activity significantly (XREF_FIG) suggests that PtdIns (3) P generated through dephosphorylation of PtdIns (3,4,5) P 3 could be controlling SGK3.
